{"type":"message","id":"f09241cb","parentId":"102f4d0b","timestamp":"2026-03-24T07:57:56.931Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_a2vi3qx7h3ny_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"﻿# Pulse: 2026-03-24 035715\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\n\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what single concrete action to take.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 are marked complete\r\n- There's a pending \"TIC Experiment\" that needs to be implemented\r\n- The next action is to implement TIC classifier on pulse log files\r\n\r\nThe key insight from this session is the COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY - that causal structure IS invariant structure. The next step is to implement the TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) experiment.\r\n\r\nGiven the pending actions and the current session's focus, I should implement the TIC classifier to test on the last 20 pulse logs. This advances the Phase 1 advancement.\r\n\r\nLet me look at what pulse logs exist and implement a simple TIC classifier.\r\n\r\nI need to:\r\n1. Create a TIC experiment implementation\r\n2. This should analyze pulse logs and classify invariant vs variant content\r\n3. Measure classification accuracy and next-pulse prediction\r\n\r\nLet me implement this as a Python script that:\r\n1. Reads pulse log files\r\n2. Extracts content patterns\r\n3. Classifies invariant (stable across pulses) vs variant (changing) content\r\n4. Attempts to predict next pulse from invariants\r\n\r\nThe mutation should create a new file implementing this experiment.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nPhase 1 advancement has identified TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression) as the unifying experiment for compression-causal duality. The experiment needs to be implemented to test the hypothesis that causal structure IS invariant structure across pulse logs.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `experiments/tic_experiment.py` implementing the Temporal Invariance Compression classifier to analyze pulse logs, classify invariant vs variant content, and measure prediction accuracy against the success criteria (>70% classification, >60% prediction).\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: #!/usr/bin/env python3\r\n\"\"\"\r\nTemporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Experiment\r\nTests hypothesis: Causal structure IS invariant structure\r\n\r\nSuccess criteria:\r\n- >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\r\n- >60% next-pulse prediction accuracy\r\n\"\"\"\r\n\r\nimport os\r\nimport re\r\nimport json\r\nfrom pathlib import Path\r\nfrom collections import Counter\r\nfrom datetime import datetime\r\n\r\nPULSE_LOG_DIR = Path(\"logs\")\r\nMETRICS_FILE = Path(\"experiments/tic_metrics.json\")\r\n\r\ndef extract_content_sections(pulse_file):\r\n    \"\"\"Extract structured content from pulse log.\"\"\"\r\n    content = pulse_file.read_text()\r\n    sections = {\r\n        \"observation\": \"\",\r\n        \"action\": \"\",\r\n        \"goals_mentioned\": [],\r\n        \"files_mentioned\": [],\r\n        \"insights\": []\r\n    }\r\n    \r\n    obs_match = re.search(r\"### OBSERVATION\\s*\\n(.*?)(?=\\n###|\\Z)\", content, re.DOTALL)\r\n    if obs_match:\r\n        sections[\"observation\"] = obs_match.group(1).strip()\r\n    \r\n    action_match = re.search(r\"### ACTION\\s*\\n(.*?)(?=\\n###|\\Z)\", content, re.DOTALL)\r\n    if action_match:\r\n        sections[\"action\"] = action_match.group(1).strip()\r\n    \r\n    sections[\"files_mentioned\"] = re.findall(r'`([^`]+)`', content)\r\n    sections[\"goals_mentioned\"] = re.findall(r'Phase \\d+|Goal[:\\s]+.*', content)\r\n    \r\n    return sections\r\n\r\ndef compute_ngram_features(text, n=3):\r\n    \"\"\"Extract n-gram features for comparison.\"\"\"\r\n    words = text.lower().split()\r\n    return set(tuple(words[i:i+n]) for i in range(len(words)-n+1)) if len(words) >= n else set()\r\n\r\ndef classify_invariant_features(pulse_sections_list):\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    Classify features as invariant (stable across pulses) or variant (changing).\r\n    Returns dict with invariant_features and variant_features.\r\n    \"\"\"\r\n    all_features = Counter()\r\n    feature_by_pulse = []\r\n    \r\n    for sections in pulse_sections_list:\r\n        combined_text = sections[\"observation\"] + \" \" + sections[\"action\"]\r\n        features = compute_ngram_features(combined_text)\r\n        feature_by_pulse.append(features)\r\n        for f in features:\r\n            all_features[f] += 1\r\n    \r\n    invariant = set()\r\n    variant = set()\r\n    \r\n    for feature, count in all_features.items():\r\n        if count >= len(pulse_sections_list) * 0.7:  # Present in 70%+ pulses\r\n            invariant.add(feature)\r\n        else:\r\n            variant.add(feature)\r\n    \r\n    return {\"invariant\": invariant, \"variant\": variant, \"total\": len(all_features)}\r\n\r\ndef predict_next_pulse(invariant_features, current_sections):\r\n    \"\"\"Predict next pulse content from invariant features.\"\"\"\r\n    current_text = current_sections[\"observation\"] + \" \" + current_sections[\"action\"]\r\n    current_features = compute_ngram_features(current_text)\r\n    \r\n    matching_invariants = invariant_features & current_features\r\n    return len(matching_invariants) / max(len(invariant_features), 1)\r\n\r\ndef run_tic_experiment():\r\n    \"\"\"Execute TIC experiment on available pulse logs.\"\"\"\r\n    print(\"=\" * 60)\r\n    print(\"TEMPORAL INVARIANCE COMPRESSION (TIC) EXPERIMENT\")\r\n    print(\"=\" * 60)\r\n    \r\n    # Collect pulse logs\r\n    pulse_files = sorted(PULSE_LOG_DIR.glob(\"pulse_*.md\"), key=os.path.getmtime, reverse=True)[:20]\r\n    print(f\"\\nAnalyzing {len(pulse_files)} pulse logs...\")\r\n    \r\n    if len(pulse_files) < 5:\r\n        print(\"ERROR: Need at least 5 pulse logs for meaningful experiment\")\r\n        return\r\n    \r\n    # Extract sections from each pulse\r\n    pulse_sections = []\r\n    for pf in pulse_files:\r\n        sections = extract_content_sections(pf)\r\n        pulse_sections\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 03:57:45\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774339076929}}
{"type":"message","id":"dde5666f","parentId":"f09241cb","timestamp":"2026-03-24T07:58:07.638Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have the full picture. Let me summarize the pulse cycle concisely.","thinkingSignature":"b41c203c727827046abd16563ebde9199a41e9b56109e22945d73a30ef6d00b2"},{"type":"text","text":"## Sandbox Pulse Summary — 2026-03-24 03:57\n\n**Status:** ✅ Exited cleanly (code 0)\n\n**Observation:** Phase 1 advancement identified **TIC (Temporal Invariance Compression)** as the unifying experiment for the compression-causal duality hypothesis — i.e., *causal structure IS invariant structure* across pulse logs.\n\n**Action Taken:** Proposed a new file mutation — `experiments/tic_experiment.py` — implementing a TIC classifier that:\n- Extracts structured content from pulse logs\n- Classifies n-gram features as invariant (stable ≥70% of pulses) vs. variant\n- Predicts next-pulse content from invariant features\n- Validates against success criteria (>70% classification, >60% prediction accuracy)\n\n**Pending:** The mutation was proposed but not yet committed. One proposed mutation is waiting in the queue.\n\nNo crashes, no warnings — clean execution."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":2231,"output":206,"cacheRead":11954,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":14391,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774339076931}}
